<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I am an 11th Minstrel on Guenevere, and here are some things for other minstrels to talk about both good and bad, and some nuetral thoughts.<P>   Firstly, there are a couple of things I would like to know more about - specifically, why I should consider upgrading my instruments if every one the merchant has is grey, yet marginally more expensive for no reasons apparantly. Second, I don't understand why I havent been able to join into any other tradeskill than tailoring - I wanted to be able to craft my own weapons, since a minstrel can use both slashing and thrusting weapons.<P>    As far as I know, the minstrel's damage spells are resisted pretty fairly overall, but do nothing against a purple mob. The stun is GREAT - it gives me plenty of time to switch from instrument to weapon, and works about 40% of the time on purples. Befudding(or more appropriatly, random pissed mode) is a spell that takes a little fiddling with in order to know when to use it. I would suggest only useing this spell when you have five or more tanks in the group, as useing it during soloing is meaningless because the spell causes the mob to attack random GROUP members, and casters generally don't have the hitpoints for toe to toe melee - on that note, use this spell in an emergency ie; the mob is on the healer for some reason - your healer will love you.<P>   If you play a minstrel, you know that you are THE faastest running class in Albion, and personally I consider it quite rude to fly past someone if they are going your way - simply invite them to run with you, and they are usually very greatful and sometimes even pay you!  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"> It's a great way to meet friends and future realm defenders.<P>   Power regen is an awesome asset to the minstrels already diverse group abilities, and it's a drum song like the motivation song(speed), so theres no switching of instruments to fiddle with - I like saying fiddle ) The charm when you get it is very rarely used, since you can only charm humanoid npc's and is a flute song, and most of what you end up fighting in a group is far from humanoid - on the bright side, if you do encounter a group of bandits, it's a wise decision to charm one, and since you'll have your flute out, you can mez for crowd control.<P>    A minstrel in melee can add exceptional damage output while in a group with tanks, especially the ones that can taunt, and especially on purple mobs that will resist your damage spells anyway, so don't be afraid to spend a couple of points into melee abilities - I chose thrusting because my initial intent was to go infiltrator, but slashing weapons are just as good as far as store-bought goes.<P>    And I have run clean out of time, so I hope to see some replys here(don't get much time to post), and I hope I've helped someone.
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
